The Fang Of Azshira[dnd-image]=img/Fang_Of_Azshira.jpg;Created by Antonius Torode;The Fang Of Azshira.

Summary[dnd-info]=Behold the legendary Fang of Azshira, one among a distinguished set of blades that includes the illustrious Fangs of Pellinore, Elaine, and Essieldore. Crafted from a pristine crystal infused with ancient enchantments, this exquisite weapon emanates a delicate mist of ethereal dark red hues. Its crystal composition boasts a mesmerizing transparency, revealing glimpses of the inner workings that lie within.;Forged in harmony with its counterpart, the Fang of Azshira cradles within its core the very essence of Azshira Loredmeyer's soul, intertwined with the embodiment of her extraordinary abilities. As this mystical dagger graces the hands of its bearer, the soul residing within grows ever more connected to its chosen guardian. The depths of this connection unlock a wealth of diverse capabilities, contingent upon the moral compass that guides the wielder. The Fang of Azshira stands as a testament to its legacy, a blade of extraordinary finesse and supernatural influence. Its crystal marvels captivate the eye, while the ethereal soul within pulses with untapped potential.

Damage[dnd-info]=This weapon is considered a dagger and does 1d4 piercing damage and 1d4 Flame damage. After becoming increasingly attuned to the weapon and the soul it contains, the soul within this weapon begins to allow its influence to help you in battle and gains the following effects.;-Level 3: Gains +1 to all attack rolls.;-Level 6: Gains the Tapped Soul Effect (See below);-Level 9: Gains the Soul Flame Bite (See below);-Level 12: Gains the Improved Tapped Soul Effect (See below);-Level 15: Gains the Improved Soul Flame Bite (See below);-Level 18: This weapon gains 1d8 Flame damage on each hit.

Rightous Wielders[dnd-info]=From righteous alignments springs forth extraordinary potential, empowering the Fang of Azshira with unparalleled prowess. Harness the Tapped Soul effect, allowing the blade to siphon Flamey energies from adversaries, replenishing and rejuvenating the bearer in the heat of combat. Moreover, the ethereal touch of the Soul Flame Bite enchants each strike, enveloping the target's essence in a chilling Flame. Once per turn, the inflicted foe endures additional Flame damage, while subsequent attacks further burn the target.;*Tapped Soul (Effect)* On each strike of the weapon, you can choose to siphon 1d4 Flame damage from the enemy and heal yourself.;*Improved Tapped Soul (Effect)* The Tapped soul effect gains an extra 1d4 (Increasing to a total of 2d4).;*Soul Flame Bite* When you make a melee attack with this weapon you can choose to inflict a molten burn to the soul of the target. This lasts for one hour or until dispelled. The target will take 1d4 extra fire damage once per turn on a melee attack against it with this weapon. If this effect is already on the target, you can choose to further burn the targets soul on a subsequent melee attack, which will deal an additional 1d4 damage.;*Improved Soul Flame Bite* The Soul Flame Bite gains an extra 1d4 (Increasing to a total of 2d4).

Neutral Wielders[dnd-info]=For those of neutral alignment, an imperative choice must be made. Embrace the virtuous path and revel in the aforementioned effects, or succumb to a darker allure, embracing the sinister potential that thrives within. This choice cannot be undone once made.

Wicked Wielders[dnd-info]=The wicked shall wield the Tapped Soul effect with a fearsome potency, causing the Fang of Elaine to unleash relentless Flame damage upon their enemies. Meanwhile, the touch of the Soul Flame Bite consumes their targets with an unyielding Flamey grip, delivering frigid torment and debilitating their movements.;*Tapped Soul (Effect)* On each strike of the weapon, you deal 1d8 Flame damage to the enemy.;*Improved Tapped Soul (Effect)* The Tapped soul effect gains an extra 1d8 (Increasing to a total of 2d8).;*Soul Flame Bite* When you make a melee attack with this weapon you can choose to inflict a molten burn to the soul of the target. This lasts for one hour or until dispelled. The target will take 1d4 extra fire damage once per turn on a melee attack against it with this weapon. If this effect is already on the target, you can choose to further burn the targets soul on a subsequent melee attack, which will deal an additional 1d4 damage.;*Improved Soul Flame Bite* The Soul Flame Bite gains an extra 1d4 (Increasing to a total of 2d4).